To convert the handwritten code into a functional website, you would need to write the HTML and JavaScript code. Here's a basic example of how you could implement the code:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Joke Website</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
  <div id="jokes">
    <div id="joke1">
      <p>Isama /bat joke 1</p>
    </div>
    <div id="joke2">
      <p>Isama /bat joke 2</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script src="joke-website.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
JavaScript (joke-website.js):
```javascript
const joke1 = document.getElementById("joke1");
const joke2 = document.getElementById("joke2");

function showJoke() {
  const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * 2);
  if (randomIndex === 0) {
    joke1.style.display = "block";
    joke2.style.display = "none";
  } else {
    joke2.style.display = "block";
    joke1.style.display = "none";
  }
}

setInterval(showJoke, 5000);
```
This code creates a simple website with a title and two jokes. The JavaScript code uses the `setInterval` function to display a random joke every 5 seconds. The jokes are hidden initially, and the `showJoke` function is called to reveal one of the jokes.
